observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
consider the provisions of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 for the one time cleansing of PPE account balances;
require the Inventory Committee to include all Public Infrastructures in the conduct of physical count of PPE;
require the Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries to drop from the books of accounts the Work/Zoo Animals, unserviceable and donated properties;
require the Property Officer to make proper disposal of unserviceable properties;
require the Property Officer to maintain complete, accurate and updated Property Cards (PCs) based on records and reconcile the same regularly with the Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELCs) maintained by the Accounting Office, and
require the Property Unit and the Accounting Office to effect the necessary adjustments in their records, if any, in order to reflect the correct balance of every PPE account.
Efficient implementation of the foregoing would redound to the corrected balances of both PPE records, thus resulting in the fair presentation of the affected accounts in the financial statements.

We recommended that management:

a.	require the Municipal Engineer to prepare an updated and corrected Report on Public Infrastructures and furnish a copy of said report to the Property and Accounting Offices;




b.	require the inventory committee to include Public Infrastructures in the conduct of physical count of PPE;




c) 	Require the GSO to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete record for all roads and components; and

d) 	Require the Municipal Accountant to record back in the appropriate PPE accounts the Public Infrastructures appearing in the registries as of December 31, 2015.

Disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the Local Road Network System of the municipality.

We recommended that management:

	a. 	Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete and accurate description and cost segregation of road components for all road projects;

	b. 	Require the inventory committee to conduct physical count of local road network system and prepare the Report on the physical Count of Road Network System;

	c) 	Require the GSO to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete record for all roads and components; and

	d) 	Require the Municipal Accountant to record back in the appropriate PPE accounts the Public Infrastructures appearing in the registries as of December 31, 2015.

Disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the Local Road Network System of the municipality.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
require the Municipal Engineer to prepare an updated and corrected Report on Public Infrastructures and furnish a copy of said report to the Property and Accounting Offices;
require the Inventory Committee to include Public Infrastructures in the conduct of physical count of PPE;
require the Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries  to drop from the books of accounts the  Work/Zoo Animals, unserviceable and donated properties;
require the Property Officer to make proper disposal of unserviceable properties;
require the Property Officer to maintain complete, accurate and updated Property Cards (PCs)  based on records and reconcile the same regularly with the Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELCs) maintained by the Accounting Office, and
require the Property Unit and the Accounting Office to effect the necessary adjustments in their records, if any, in order to reflect the correct balance of every PPE account.

We recommended and management agreed to:
Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete and accurate description and cost segregation of road components for all road projects;
Require the inventory committee to conduct physical count of local road network system and prepare the  Report on the physical Count of Road Network System;
Require the GSO to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete record for all roads and components; and
Require the Municipal Accountant to record back in the appropriate PPE accounts the Public Infrastructures appearing in the registries as of December 31, 2015 and to disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the Local Road Network System of the municipality.

conduct detailed engineering investigations including right of way acquisitions  and consider appropriate timing/phasing of the implementation of the project before the conduct of bidding and award of contract for infrastructure projects;
consider the topography of the region, weather condition and prevalence of typhoons thereat in the determination of the contract time and the period of project implementation; and
issue suspension orders to contractors only when necessary and when the reasons are fully supported by documents and duly validated.

We recommended that management:

a.	require the reconciliation of property and accounting records on every PPE account classification and effect the necessary adjustments, if any;

b.	require the Property Unit to maintain complete, accurate and up-dated Property Cards (PCs) and reconcile the same regularly with the Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELCs) maintained by the Accounting Office;

c.	require the property custodian to file the PARs/AREs of all movable non- expendable properties and cause the renewal of the same every January of the 3rd year after issue in order to facilitate the physical count of PPE and to easily identify the official/employee responsible in case of loss, resignation, or expiration of term of office;

d.	require the posting of property tag/number on the prominent portion of every movable non expendable property/equipment, and

e.	proper disposal of unserviceable properties be made.

We recommended that management:

	a. 	require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;

	b. 	require the inventory committee to conduct physical count of its local road network system and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Road Network System;

	require the GSO to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete record for all roads in its component;

	require the Municipal Accountant to record back in the appropriate PPE accounts the Public Infrastructures appearing in the registries as of December 31, 2015 and to disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the Local Road Network System of the municipality.

